


                         / Flask Boilerplate /

                 a flask boilerplate application

      1. Install virtual env

      2. create virtualenv
      virtualenv env
      source env/bin/activate

      3. install requirements
      pip install -r requirements

    ~ How do I use it?

      4. edit the configuration in the flaskr.py file or
         export an  environment variable
         pointing to a configuration file.

      5. Instruct flask to use the right application

         export FLASK_APP=app.py
         export FLASK_DEBUG=1

      6. initialize the database with this command:

         flask initdb

      7. now you can run flaskr:

         flask run

         the application will greet you on
         http://localhost:5000/

    ~ Is it tested?

      You betcha.  Run the `test_app.py` file to see
      the tests pass.
